        <img src="acelogo.png" style="width: 40px; margin-top: 20px; display: inline-block;">
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat; color: #e60f0f; display: inline-block; position: absolute; margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">An Ace Airlines News Story</p>
        <h1 style="font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 900; font-size: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">Ace Airlines Reopens flights to all destinations.</h1>
        <p style="width: 100px; height: 20px; background-color: #e60f0f; border-radius: 4px; color: white;font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 5px;">May 15, 2020</p>
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat;">In a recent press announcement Ace Airlines said that they will be reopening all destinations. "We have looked at the data and have decided that it will be safe for us to resume flights to all Ace Airlines destinations." If this does not go according to plan, then we will temporarily stop flights to certain destinations.</p>

        <img src="acelogo.png" style="width: 40px; margin-top: 20px; display: inline-block;">
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat; color: #e60f0f; display: inline-block; position: absolute; margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">An Ace Airlines News Story</p>
        <h1 style="font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 900; font-size: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">Coronavirus stops flights from many popular Ace Airlines destinations</h1>
        <p style="width: 100px; height: 20px; background-color: #e60f0f; border-radius: 4px; color: white;font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 5px;">April 8, 2020</p>
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat;">ACE AIRLINES - Because of the novel virus, Coronavirus, Ace Airlines has had to cease the departure of flights from many of their most poplar destinations. Flights arriving/departing from Seattle, Washington and Atlanta, Georgia have been temporarilly removed from Ace's list of destinations. However, as the virus keeps growing stronger, officials at Ace Airlines seem that the shutdown of Ace is inevitable. Ben Lambertson, CEO of Ace Airlines said, "We are doing the best that we can on this issue, and hope to get the airline back up and running in no time." We will keep you informed on the state of the airline during this period of Coronavirus.</p>

        <img src="acelogo.png" style="width: 40px; margin-top: 20px; display: inline-block;">
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat; color: #e60f0f; display: inline-block; position: absolute; margin-left: 10px; margin-top: 20px;">An Ace Airlines News Story</p>
        <h1 style="font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 900; font-size: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">What Ace Airlines is doing about COVID-19.</h1>
        <p style="width: 100px; height: 20px; background-color: #e60f0f; border-radius: 4px; color: white;font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 5px;">April 2, 2020</p>
        <p style="font-family: Montserrat;">Here at Ace Airlines, your safety is our priority. In the current world-wide situation we are taking action to ensure that our customers and employees are safe. Here are just a few of the measures that we are taking. To slow the spread of COVID-19 Ace Airlines will be limiting flights to certain destinations. Some destinations will temporarily not be served. These destinations include the following: New York, California, Florida, and Washington. When you arrive at the airport you will use Ace Interface to check-in and print your boarding pass. The device used will be wiped down after each use. To avoid the spread of germs in flight we will not be refilling drinks with the same cup. We will also limit touching other items that come in contact with customers. Once the plane is at the gate we will go through the cabin and wipe down all tray tables, door handles, and window grips. This will ensure that the seat will be clean for the next passenger. These are just a few of the precautions that we are taking. If you have any questions please feel free to contact us at aceairofficial@gmail.com</p>
         <p style="width: 100%; height: 20px; background-color: #e60f0f; border-radius: 10px; color: white;font-family: Montserrat; text-align: center; font-size: 12px; padding-top: 5px; margin-top: 20px;margin-bottom: 20px;">MORE ARTICLES COMING SOON</p>
      </div>
    </div>
